(133-1) Q: We are men living in the world and have one kind of grief or another. We pray for help and still are not satisfied. What to do? A: Trust God. If you surrender you must be able to abide by His will and not make a grievance of what may not please you. Things may turn out different from what they are in appearance. Distress often leads men to faith in God.
(133-2) Q: I am a sinful man! A: Why think of yourself so? You have rightly thrown all responsibility on God in whom you have faith and He will look after that.
