(179-1) Q: Why should not the Maharshi help the masses by lecturing to them? A: Is not God working? Is He making speeches? Can work be done only through speech? Do you know the amount of work that can be silently turned out without any speech? (179-2) See the mind. You must stand aloof from it. You are not the mind and the Self will remain over.
(179-3) Maharshi told Dandapani, after the latter had related a vivid clairvoyant dream, wherein Maharshi appeared to him and answered certain questions for him: "You were very anxious to know these answers and it was your own self which supplied them to you. I have no knowledge of having visited you."
